    "title": "The Cyrillic Code I",
    "subtitle": "True Friends & False Friends",
    "description": "Master the alphabet through logical groupings: True Friends (same look, same sound) and False Friends (Latin look, different sound)",
    "objectives": [
      "Recognize Cyrillic letters that look like Latin letters",
      "Identify 'False Friend' letters that look Latin but sound different",
      "Read 20 international words in Cyrillic",
      "Understand the phonetic logic behind Cyrillic"
    ],
    "grammarFocus": ["Cyrillic alphabet groups 1-3", "Phonetic basics"],
    "totalDuration": 45,
    "transliterationMode": "full",
    "tags": ["alphabet", "basics", "cyrillic", "cognates"],
    "version": 1,
    "createdAt": "2025-11-29T00:00:00Z",
    "modifiedAt": "2025-11-29T00:00:00Z",
    "phases": [
      {
        "id": "phase-warmup",
        "name": "warm-up",
        "duration": 5,
        "items": [
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Why Cyrillic Isn't Scary\n\nCyrillic was designed for Slavic sounds. Many letters come from Greek, which is why some look familiar. The key: don't trust your eyes—trust the logic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "phase-presentation",
        "name": "presentation",
        "duration": 15,
        "items": [
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Group 1: True Friends\n\nThese letters look AND sound like their Latin equivalents:\n\n• А а = A (as in 'father')\n• Е е = E (as in 'bet')\n• І і = I (as in 'machine')\n• О о = O (as in 'hot')\n• К к = K\n• М м = M\n• Т т = T"
          },
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Group 2: False Friends (DANGER!)\n\nThese letters LOOK Latin but sound DIFFERENT:\n\n• В в = V (not B!)\n• Н н = N (not H!)\n• Р р = R (not P!) - trilled\n• С с = S (not C!)\n• У у = U (not Y!)\n• Х х = KH (not X!) - like 'Bach'"
          },
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Group 3: New but Easy\n\nLetters that don't exist in Latin but are straightforward:\n\n• Б б = B (like a belly with a hat)\n• Д д = D\n• З з = Z\n• Л л = L\n• П п = P (like a doorway/portal)\n• Ф ф = F"
          },
          { "type": "activity", "activityId": "act-uk-A1-01-match" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "phase-practice",
        "name": "practice",
        "duration": 15,
        "items": [
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Reading Practice\n\nLet's read international words. Sound out each letter using what you've learned."
          },
          { "type": "activity", "activityId": "act-uk-A1-01-quiz" },
          { "type": "activity", "activityId": "act-uk-A1-01-sort" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "phase-production",
        "name": "production",
        "duration": 10,
        "items": [
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Real-World Reading\n\nTry reading these words without looking at the transliteration first:\n\n1. БАНК\n2. ПАРК\n3. МЕТРО\n4. ПІЦА\n5. СТУДЕНТ"
          },
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "Remember\n\nП = P, Р = R, В = V, Н = N, С = S, Х = KH"
          },
          {
            "type": "canvas",
            "canvasData": "{}",
            "teacherNotes": "⚠️ ITALIC WARNING ⚠️\n\nCyrillic italic/cursive looks VERY different from print!\n\nDangerous letters:\n• т → looks like \"m\" in italic\n• п → looks like \"n\" in italic\n• д → looks like \"g\" in italic\n• и → looks like \"u\" in italic\n• л → looks like \"л\" with a hook\n• г → looks like \"∂\" in italic\n\nWe'll cover this in Module 02!"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
